        BuzzFeed is seeking an organized and ambitious Editorial Project Coordinator to support our ever-growing edit staff. The position is based in our NYC office, and we offer competitive compensation, benefits, and an employee stock option program -- not to mention a super collaborative work environment!
        The ideal candidate is someone who can handle working on projects of varying size. This person is a self-starter who takes pride in being detail-oriented but can also pivot when necessary to meet the needs of the team. Most of all, we're looking for someone who's excited to come to work every day and figure out how to help their teams get great things done!
        The Editorial Project Coordinator will work closely with the Managing Editor and help support the team in an administrative capacity, managing everything from calendars to budgets, along with anticipating the logistical needs of a growing office. This is a great opportunity for anyone looking to learn more about online publishing and operations at a fast-growing media company.
        Responsibilities:
        * Coordinate/manage mid to large-scale editorial projects
        * Use data to track success and provide insights for future projects
        * Provide general support to the Managing Editor and edit team with day-to-day administrative tasks, including managing calendars, planning team events and booking travel
        * Work with the Operations Associate to anticipate the needs of new staff and maintaining a fun, organized atmosphere
        Requirements:
        * Proven organizational and administrative skills, showing a precise attention to detail
        * Experience working for a print or online publishing company
        * Ability to multitask and anticipate needs
        * Confidence in a fast paced environment and with a good amount of autonomy
        * Emotional intelligence and a sense of humor
        About BuzzFeed
        BuzzFeed is the leading independent digital media and tech company delivering news and entertainment content to a global audience. We have offices in 18 cities around the world and more than 1300 employees including reporters, video producers, data scientists, engineers, brand strategists, and more. We infuse hard work and fun though a culture of experimentation, teamwork, equality, and humble confidence. As an employee, you'll enjoy perks like office events, snacks, career development courses, and no work on your birthday! But most importantly, you'll work with inspiring colleagues to build tools and create content that helps connect people all over the world.